conbody.p: Create an angular dimension by selecting an entity or specifying the vertex and both sides of the angle. The dimension is based on the current dimension style. Options allow you to specify the angle and contents of the dimension text.

section.title: Methods to create an angular dimension
section.p: There are two methods to begin creating an angular dimension:

dlentry.dd: Begin creating an angular dimension by selecting a line, arc, or circle to dimension then:
If you selected a line or line segment
Specify the location of the dimension arc.
If you selected an arc or arc segment
Specify the location of the dimension arc.
Specify a point to define one side of the angle. The point where you first selected the circle defines the other side of the angle.
Specify the location of the dimension arc.
Begin creating an angular dimension by specifying the vertex of the angle then:
Specify a point to define one side of the angle.
Specify a point to define the other side of the angle.
Specify the location of the dimension arc.

section.title: Options within the DIMANGULAR command
section.p: After you begin creating an angular dimension, the following options may be available:

dlentry.dd: Specify the angle of the dimension text. A value of 0 aligns the dimension text with the dimension line. Any other value rotates the dimension text relative to the x-axis of the current UCS.

Enter text to override the default dimension text which includes the measured length of the dimension. You can use two angle brackets <> to display the measured length of the dimension in addition to other text.
